# Momentum: complete shipping plan

## Product scope and principles

- **Audience:** One **single cohort** of developers; **all tasks are cohort-visible** (no private task lists in v1).
- **Time structure:** Work is **sectioned by week** (`Week` rows: theme title, `startsAt`, `endsAt`, optional `sortIndex`). “Current week” drives LLM context and Friday Launch filters.
- **Feel:** Arcade / IDE energy—horizontal conveyors, glass panels, motion with discipline (see Motion).
- **Design system:** Implement **semantic color roles** early (`ship`, `focus`, `github`, `ai`, `danger`, `surface`) so Ship green vs focus blue do not collide with GitHub vs AI card accents. **Fine-grained visual polish** can wait until your external design artifacts land; tokens and layout should not.

## Streak rules (authoritative)

Implement exactly in server logic and tests:

1. **Any ship counts** toward completing work (task moves to `shipped`, confetti, Discord, fuel gauge, etc.).
2. **Streak increments at most once per calendar day** on **streak-eligible days** (next bullet).
3. **Weekends do not count** for streak: **Saturday and Sunday** (in the **cohort timezone**, chosen once and stored as config—e.g. `America/Chicago`) **never increment** `currentStreak` / `highestStreak`, even if the user ships.
4. On an eligible weekday, the **first ship of that local day** may increment streak **by 1** if it follows consecutive eligible days with at least one qualifying ship; **subsequent ships the same day** do not add again.

**Suggested persisted fields on `User`:** `currentStreak`, `highestStreak`, `lastStreakIncrementLocalDate` (date-only string in cohort TZ), and optionally `lastShipAt` for analytics. **Optional `ShipEvent` row** per ship for Discord replay, audits, and debugging failed webhooks.

## Architecture (high level)

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph client [NextClient]
    Board[AssemblyLine]
    Radar[CommandCenter]
    Slot[SlotModal]
  end
  subgraph server [ServerActions_RouteHandlers]
    GH[GitHubAppOctokit]
    LLM[AI_generateObject]
    RL[UpstashRateLimit]
    DB[(Postgres_Prisma)]
  end
  subgraph external [External]
    GitHub[GitHub_API]
    OpenAI[OpenAI_or_Anthropic]
    Discord[Discord_Webhook]
  end
  Board --> DB
  Radar --> DB
  Slot --> RL
  Slot --> GH
  Slot --> LLM
  GH --> GitHub
  LLM --> OpenAI
  ShipFlow[shipTask_transaction] --> DB
  ShipFlow --> Discord
```

## Progress log (maintained)

**2026-05-14 — Plan completion: slot save, transactional ship, Discord, Friday, observability**

- **Slot orchestration:** `prefetchSlotBundle` server action wraps GitHub + LLM prefetches in `Promise.allSettled`. Slot modal uses client `Promise.allSettled` with arm delay; per-reel **Retry**; **Save to board** calls `saveSpunTask` with `crypto.randomUUID()` idempotency key (Prisma unique → idempotent success on double-submit).
- **Ship flow:** `shipTask` Prisma transaction sets `shipped` + `shippedAt`, applies **cohort-timezone** weekday streak rules from `ShipEvent` history (`src/lib/streak-ship.ts`), inserts `ShipEvent`, updates user streak fields. Client **optimistic** column move + inline error on failure; **motion burst** “confetti” on success (reduced-motion skips burst).
- **Discord:** `src/lib/discord-webhook.ts` posts roll (task accept) + ship embeds; env `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_ROLL_URL` / `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_SHIP_URL`; failures logged without rolling back ship.
- **Friday Launch:** `/friday` masonry grid + `toggleVote` (Upstash vote rate limit in prod); `getFridayLaunch` loads active-week shipped tasks with vote counts.
- **Cross-cutting:** `logServerEvent` JSON lines for ship/save/vote/discord; `DashboardRefresh` polls `router.refresh()` every 30s on the home board.
- **Agent / deploy docs:** `.cursor/rules/momentum.mdc` mirrors `.cursorrules` for Cursor Rules; `.env.example` extended with Discord + `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` + smoke checklist. Vitest covers `streak-calendar` prev-eligible helper.

**2026-05-14 — Slot LLM: generateObject + Upstash + audit log**

- **Server-only:** `invokeSlotLlmIdeas` in `src/lib/llm-slot-spin.ts` — Vercel AI SDK `generateObject` with Zod (`slotIdeasSchema`: exactly three ideas × title / oneLiner / suggestedScope), `maxRetries: 0`, **5s** `AbortController` timeout.
- **Rate limit:** `@upstash/ratelimit` sliding window **5 / 60s** keyed by `userId`. **Production** requires `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` + `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`; **development** skips limit with a one-time console warning if unset.
- **Audit:** Every gated outcome writes `LlmInvocationLog` with `promptVersionHash` = SHA-256 of system prompt + `SLOT_LLM_SCHEMA_VERSION`, `model`, `ok`, `errorCode` (`rate_limited`, `aborted`, `schema_error`, `provider_error`, `ratelimit_unconfigured`), `durationMs`.
- **Prefetch:** `prefetchSlotLlmIdeas` server action; slot modal runs it in parallel with GitHub prefetch + arm delay. Tech / Output reels map from the first two generated ideas when configured.

## Revisit later

- **GitHub App setup:** When you are ready, finish org app install and fill `GITHUB_APP_ID`, `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`, `GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID`, and `GITHUB_APP_REPO_ALLOWLIST` (see `.env.example`). OAuth sign-in is separate; the App drives allowlisted issue fetch for the Source reel (`src/lib/github-app-issues.ts`).

**2026-05-14 — GitHub App allowlist + quick-win fetch (Phase 3 start)**

- **Server-only:** `octokit` + `@octokit/auth-app` installation auth; `fetchQuickWinGithubIssues` in `src/lib/github-app-issues.ts` (import `server-only`). Env: `GITHUB_APP_ID`, `GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY`, `GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID`, `GITHUB_APP_REPO_ALLOWLIST` (comma `owner/repo`), optional `GITHUB_APP_ISSUE_LABEL` (default `quick-win`).
- **Allowlist:** Parses and queries only listed repos; `Promise.allSettled` per repo with `partialErrors` aggregated. Pull requests filtered out; caps per repo / total to avoid huge payloads.
- **Prefetch:** `prefetchGithubQuickWins` server action (`src/actions/github-quick-wins.ts`) requires sign-in before calling GitHub (anonymous users skip API). Slot modal waits for min arm delay **and** prefetch; on success, Source reel shows the first candidate title/repo ref; failures surface a short hint without leaking secrets.

**2026-05-14 — Phase 2 views: assembly line, command center, slot modal**

- **Assembly line:** Horizontal three-zone conveyor (`incoming` / `in_progress` / `shipped`) with semantic GitHub vs AI card chrome, optional GitHub links, per-column empty states, and conveyor stripe motion gated by the existing reduced-motion toggle + `prefers-reduced-motion` (Tailwind `animate-conveyor`).
- **Command center:** Fuel meter = shipped ÷ active-week scoped tasks (0% when no week tasks); stretch bar vs `COHORT_WEEK_SHIP_TARGET` (`src/lib/momentum-constants.ts`). Radar places each cohort member by angle with radius from personal week shipped ÷ assigned week tasks (outer “idle” when no week assignments).
- **Slot machine:** `SlotMachineModal` replaces the placeholder—three reels, prefetch skeleton with mock latency, spin reshuffle, `useLayoutEffect` to avoid open flicker, reduced-motion fast path.
- **Data:** `getCohortDashboard` (`src/lib/cohort-dashboard.ts`) loads cohort tasks (active week + `weekId: null` backlog), members, and week fuel counts. Seed creates demo tasks when the DB has none (`prisma/seed.ts`).

**2026-05-14 — Phase 1 foundation in repo; app smoke-tested**

- **Stack:** Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind, Framer Motion, Prisma + PostgreSQL, Auth.js v5 with **GitHub OAuth** (user identity + Prisma adapter). Next pinned to a patched 15.3.x line for RSC advisory.
- **Database:** Schema applied with `npx prisma db push` on a new empty DB (e.g. Vercel/Prisma Postgres). Seed creates cohort **`cursor-boston`** (timezone `America/Chicago`) and an **active week** titled *Week 1 — Foundation*. New users are attached to the first cohort on `createUser`.
- **Env (documented in `.env.example`):** `DATABASE_URL` must be `postgresql://` or `postgres://`; `AUTH_SECRET` (or `NEXTAUTH_SECRET`); `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID` / `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET`. Dev allows a temporary `AUTH_SECRET` placeholder with a console warning.
- **UI shell:** Dark `#0F1115`-aligned surface, nav with profile + streak readout, floating **Pull the Lever** CTA, **slot modal placeholder** (real reels + data in Phase 2). **`prefers-reduced-motion`** plus in-app **Reduce motion** toggle (localStorage).
- **Friction we hit (resolved):** invalid `DATABASE_URL` protocol; missing tables until `db push`; Auth `MissingSecret`; Framer `motion.button` + invalid `pointerEvents` prop (use Tailwind `pointer-events-auto`). Windows `EPERM` during npm/prisma generate may require closing dev server before `prisma generate`.
- **Verified:** GitHub login works; home shows **Cursor Boston Cohort** and **Week 1 — Foundation** after seed.
- **ShipEvent:** added with transactional `shipTask` (Phase 3–4). **GitHub App** for issue listing is Phase 3; Phase 1 uses **OAuth App** for sign-in only.

## Phase 1: Foundation, auth, and data model (expanded)

**1.1 Project bootstrap**

- Next.js **App Router**, **Tailwind**, **Framer Motion**, **Prisma** + **Postgres** (Supabase or Vercel Postgres recommended for auth/realtime compatibility).
- **Auth (required for v1):** Prefer **Supabase Auth** (magic link) or **GitHub OAuth** so every `User` maps to a real principal. Single-cohort still needs identity for assignments, rate limits, votes, and audit logs.

**1.2 Core entities**

- **`Cohort`:** Single row for now (`slug`, `name`, `timezone` for week/streak boundaries).
- **`Week`:** `cohortId`, `title` (theme), `startsAt`, `endsAt`, `isActive` or infer active by date.
- **`User`:** Profile fields + streak fields (see Streak rules).
- **`Task`:** `title`, `description`, `source` (`github` | `ai`), `status` (`incoming` | `in_progress` | `shipped`), `themeTag`, `weekId` (nullable until slotted), `assigneeUserId` (nullable), **`shippedAt`** (nullable), **GitHub columns** (all nullable for AI tasks): `githubOwner`, `githubRepo`, `githubIssueNumber`, `githubNodeId`, `githubHtmlUrl`, **`metadata` JSON** for extra payload, **`idempotencyKey` UNIQUE** (client UUID for spin saves).
- **`CohortSettings` or fields on `Cohort`:** pointer to **current week** or derive from `Week` table.
- **`LlmInvocationLog`:** `id`, `userId`, `promptVersionHash`, `model`, `ok`, `errorCode`, `durationMs`, `createdAt` (never store raw prompts in client-accessible code paths; server only).
- **`Vote`:** `userId`, `taskId`, `createdAt`, **unique (userId, taskId)** for Friday upvotes; index by `taskId`.

**1.3 Global shell**

- Dark wrapper `#0F1115`, top nav with **profile + streak flame**, floating **“Pull the Lever”** CTA opening the slot modal.
- **Reduced motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` and add a **user-toggle** (localStorage) that disables non-essential Framer Motion (stripes, radar drift, slot spin visuals) while keeping functional transitions.

**1.4 Sequencing tweak (locked in)**

- Ship **`shippedAt`**, **GitHub identity columns**, **Week**, **idempotency**, **streak fields**, and **LLM log table** in **Phase 1** so Phases 3–4 avoid painful migrations.

**Phase 1 — codebase status (2026-05-14):** Items **1.1–1.3** implemented; **1.4** schema fields and tables landed (`Task` with GitHub columns, `idempotencyKey`, `Vote`, `LlmInvocationLog`, `ShipEvent`; `User` streak fields). **Slot modal** is wired with prefetch, allSettled orchestration, per-reel retry, and idempotent save.

## Phase 2: Core views (build for real use, fast turnaround)

Assume **realistic data volume**, **skeletons**, and **empty states** from the start.

**2.1 Assembly Line (board)**

- Horizontal scroll, three zones: **Incoming**, **In the Works**, **Shipped**; subtle animated stripes (CSS-first where possible).
- **Task cards:** semantic borders (`github` vs `ai` roles); drag or explicit actions to move columns if you use DnD—keep server as source of truth.
- **Cohort visibility:** board reads all cohort tasks; optional filter by week.

**2.2 Command Center**

- **Fuel gauge:** % of **week target** or % of tasks in `shipped` for active week (define one rule in code constants).
- **Radar:** avatars as soft dots; distance-to-center maps to **non-competitive** progress signal (e.g., fraction of personal week tasks shipped or column-based proximity—pick one formula and document it). Must remain legible on `#0F1115` (contrast).

**2.3 Slot Machine modal**

- Glassmorphic center modal; three reels (Source, Tech/Scope, Output).
- **Prefetch:** On modal open (or lever click), **quietly start** GitHub + LLM fetches in the background so SPIN is often instant or only animating reveal.
- **Motion:** Full Framer Motion for spin; **degraded path** when reduced motion is on (instant settle or short crossfade).

## Phase 3: Integrations and game mechanics

**3.1 GitHub (cohort model — no PAT)**

- Implement a **GitHub App** installed on your **organization**.
- Server-only: **`@octokit/auth-app`** → installation access token; restrict to **allowlisted** `owner/repo` pairs from env or DB.
- Server action / route handler: list **open issues** with label **`quick-win`** for allowlisted repos; map to internal `Task` shape with full **identity + `html_url`**.

**3.2 LLM idea generator (hardened)**

- **Vercel AI SDK** **`generateObject`** with a strict **Zod** schema (e.g., exactly three ideas with title + one-liner + suggested scope).
- **`@upstash/ratelimit`:** e.g. **5 spins per minute per user** (keyed by auth user id).
- **`AbortController`** with **5s** deadline per invocation.
- Persist **`promptVersionHash`** (hash of system prompt template + schema version string) on **`LlmInvocationLog`** for reproducibility and debugging.

**3.3 Slot orchestration**

- Use **`Promise.allSettled`** for GitHub fetch and LLM generation—**never `Promise.all`** so one failure does not nuke the other reel.
- **Per-reel UI:** show partial results + explicit retry for failed reel.
- **Save spun task:** Server validates payload; **`idempotencyKey`** from client **`crypto.randomUUID()`**; **`CREATE` with unique constraint** so double-clicks / retries do not duplicate rows.

**3.4 Ship It (single transactional story)**

- One server path (transaction): validate task + permissions → set `status`, **`shippedAt`**, apply **streak rules** in cohort TZ → insert **`ShipEvent`** (optional) → commit.
- **Client:** trigger **confetti only after** successful response; on failure, **rollback optimistic column move** + **toast**.
- **Discord Ship webhook** may be Phase 4, but **emit a domain event or queue hook** from the same transaction boundary where possible; if Discord fails, **log and optionally retry** without rolling back the ship (user-visible ship is source of truth).

## Phase 4: Discord hype engine and Friday Launch

**4.1 Webhook utility**

- Centralize Discord POST; **secrets in env**; plan for **rotation**; handle **429/400** with logging; never expose webhook URL to client.

**4.2 Messages**

- **Roll webhook:** when user **accepts** a spun task → cohort-friendly copy with user mention handle and task title + link.
- **Ship webhook:** rich embed with link; **reactions** are a **human** feature on the message—**do not depend on reading reactions** without a **Discord bot + gateway** (out of scope unless you add later).

**4.3 Friday Launch dashboard**

- Masonry of **Launch Cards** for tasks with **`shippedAt`** in the **active week window** (cohort timezone).
- **Upvotes** via **`Vote`** table; **rate limit** vote endpoint; one vote per user per task.

## Cross-cutting requirements

- **Observability:** structured logs for GitHub, LLM, Discord, and rate-limit denials (no secrets in logs).
- **Optional realtime:** Supabase Realtime or **short polling** on board/radar for “alive” cohort feel—optional for v1 if timeboxed.
- **Security:** all external APIs and tokens **server-only**; validate user belongs to cohort on every mutation.
- **Agent ergonomics:** fix **`.cursorrules`** filename typo so tooling consistently loads philosophy and stack.

## Definition of Done (site shipped)

- Authenticated user can **open slot**, see **GitHub + AI** options with **graceful partial failure**, **save** without duplicates, **move/ship** tasks with **correct streak behavior** Mon–Fri cohort TZ.
- **Assembly Line + Command Center + Friday** pages usable on real data for **one cohort**, **week-scoped** themes.
- **Discord Roll + Ship** fire reliably with basic retry/logging.
- **Reduced motion** respected + toggle.
- **Deployed** (e.g. Vercel) with **documented env vars** and a **smoke checklist** (login, spin, ship, vote, webhook).

## Risk register (short)

- **GitHub App** setup (permissions, installation id, private key handling in deployment) is the highest fixed cost—do it early in Phase 3 before UI polish depends on live issue shapes.
- **Timezone correctness** for streaks and weeks—unit-test edge cases around midnight and DST for the chosen IANA zone.
- **LLM latency**—prefetch + short timeout + partial UI prevents “stuck SPIN.”
